{
  "stem": "16930.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 297.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, we-- there was-- hakhshara didn't have any agriculture themselves.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we were-- we went out to work for different farmers, one or two people from each different farmer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say in that particular one, there were many hakhsharat in England.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These was from Chabad, also from the Mizrachi, [NON-ENGLISH], which is a religious-- the-- the organization senior to B'nai Akiva.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "B'nai Akiva graduated [INAUDIBLE] from 18 into [NON-ENGLISH], which-- and the organization of religious Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this particular hakhshara, I'm going to say about maybe 40, 50 people, maybe half women, half men.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the men were-- lived separately and the women lived separately.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To-- for prepare for-- hakhshara means preparation, preparations for Israel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In those days, you thought of Israel in terms of agriculture.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There wasn't much else there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so-- and then, of course, one or two people got these affidavits to go to Israel, just one or two.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then '48-- then in '48, of course, things changed and Israel became a Jewish state.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we went on Aliyah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That means going up to Israel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When you go to Israel, you say-- Aliyah means going up, because Israel is regarded as the central focal point.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you go off to Israel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so we went on Aliyah illegally.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was still then the illegal Aliyah.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The British still after May still were controlling the ports, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they didn't-- and so on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And so we-- and they certainly wouldn't have let people out of England to go to Israel, because they were against it at the time.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we went officially to-- to Switzerland, on vacation to Switzerland, on a few weeks' vacation, so we had all these working clothes and things and boots and things.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
